name: Tsubaki Takizakura Girls' High School Idol Club
japanese_name: 椿滝桜女学院高等学校スクールアイドル部
romanized_name: Tsubaki Takizakura Jogakuin Kōtō Gakkō Sukūru Aidoru-bu
description: The Tsubaki Takizakura Girls' High School Idol Club is a school idol group co-formed by Kyoka Takizawa and Madoka Tsubaki. They are the school idol group of Tsubaki Takizakura Girls' High School following the combined annexation of the two schools and the merging of their idol clubs in the series finale. The group consists of fifteen to eighteen members.
